# Layout Width Standard

Follow [app/Main.tsx](mdc:app/Main.tsx) for all new or updated page sections. This keeps content aligned with Header (`components/Header.tsx`) and Footer (`components/SiteFooter.tsx`).

## Section container (canonical)

Use this on every **section inner wrapper** (not on `<main>` when sections already define width):

```tsx
const SECTION = "mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6"
```

Equivalent inline classes are acceptable; prefer extracting `SECTION` when a file has multiple sections (as in `Main.tsx`).

## Root layout

- `app/[locale]/layout.tsx` `<main>`: **full width** — `min-h-[54vh] w-full overflow-x-hidden`. Do **not** put `max-w-7xl` or horizontal padding on root `main`; sections own width and padding.
- Segment layouts (blog, privacy, tags, terms): may use `main` with `mx-auto min-h-[54vh] max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6` when the page has no per-section wrappers.

## Header / footer

- Header row: `mx-auto flex w-full max-w-7xl … px-4 sm:px-6`
- Footer inner: `mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6` (footer may add `lg:px-8` if already present)

## Inner content (optional)

- Full-bleed tools (e.g. downloader): `w-full` inside `SECTION` — no extra `max-w-*` on PC.
- Long prose / FAQ / how-to lists: may use `max-w-3xl` on mobile and `lg:max-w-7xl` on large screens for readability while the **section** stays `max-w-7xl`.
- Hero titles: `max-w-xl` center on mobile, `lg:max-w-7xl` when appropriate.

## Do not

- Stack `max-w-7xl` on both root `main` and section wrappers (double constraint / misaligned padding).
- Use `max-w-6xl`, `max-w-screen-xl`, or arbitrary widths for primary page sections without explicit user request.
- Remove horizontal padding from sections; always include `px-4 sm:px-6` on the 7xl container.
